      <hedline>
        <hl1>When Tax Cuts Turn Into 'Warfare'</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Peter Scotto letter on Republican double standard on tax cuts for the wealthy and for everyone else</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Bob Herbert is right about the Republican double standard (''This Is Class Warfare?'', column, Aug. 21).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Bob Herbert is right about the Republican double standard (''This Is Class Warfare?'', column, Aug. 21).</p>
        <p>As long as the Republicans are handing out huge tax breaks to the wealthy, that's ''sound economic policy.'' The moment anyone suggests doing something for the rest of us, then it becomes ''class warfare.''</p>
        <p>PETER SCOTTO  South Hadley, Mass., Aug. 21, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
